<b>VERY suddenly, I became Saved!</b>  I remember turning to her and telling
her that we needed to leave the theater and to find a Church nearby, as
I wanted to get Baptized!  (I had been Baptized twice as a child, without
actually knowing what was going on.  At a picnic at Cedar Lake, Indiana,
some man [who must have been a Minister] took several of us little kids
wading out into the lake, and then he came up behind me and flipped
me over backwards to nearly drown me under water.  I came up coughing
as I was full of water, very confused, and terrified.  For some years, I
was very negative regarding whatever Christianity was.)<p>

From age 19 on, I was a pretty solid Christian, although I was often very
disappointed in a number of individual Churches and Ministers.<p>

