where I squeezed several hundred of those scholarly Christian articles
to fit on a 1.44 MB floppy diskette, along with the de-compression
programming and formatting.  I then bought a hundred blank floppy diskettes
and put all that scholarly Christian information on the floppy diskettes.
Between 1992 to 1996, I created and handed out around 400 of those floppy
diskettes, to anyone who I thought might benefit from the information.
I refused accepting any payment for the floppy diskettes and so I spent
around $400 in buying all those blank floppy diskettes.  I have no idea
how many people ever actually stuck the floppy diskettes in their
computers, and I always hoped that at least a few did.  The program I
created was self-loading and self-starting, so anyone who tried to
look at the 'BELIEVE Floppy Diskette' would see a list of Christian
